# Protected Files - Do Not Modify

Do not delete or modify the files in the `LICENSES` directory.

# Project Guidance

Read and follow [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) for:
- Primary references (PRD, CONTRIBUTING, architecture diagrams)
- Conventions (TDD, SOLID, Unix philosophy, no unsafe code)
- Quick links (exit codes, config precedence, adding plugins, etc.)

# TDD for AI Agents

AI agents: when adding or changing behavior, write tests first, confirm they
fail, then implement. Do not write implementation before tests. (Human
contributors: TDD is preferred but not required.) See AGENTS.md and
CONTRIBUTING.md § Test-driven development.

# Writing style

Do not use em dashes or en dashes in code comments or documentation.
Use `--` for em dashes and `-` for en dashes.

# SPDX headers

When adding SPDX headers manually, include a trailing blank line (not a
commented one) after the block so REUSE automation does not replace existing
header comments.
